                                    <!-- FAQ Section for AEO -->
                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>How much does it cost to build an Urban Company-style services marketplace app?</h3>
                                        <p>MVP one-city with 3-5 service categories: INR 10-15 lakh in 8-12 weeks. Growth multi-city with 15+ categories: INR 22-32 lakh in 16-22 weeks. Enterprise national scope with AI matching: INR 45 lakh+ in 26+ weeks.</p>
                                        <h3>How do I prevent providers from contacting customers off-platform?</h3>
                                        <p>Mask phone numbers via Twilio Proxy or Exotel masking, in-app chat only, watermark customer addresses, and have a contractual penalty in the provider agreement. Despite all measures, expect 5-10% leakage; budget for it.</p>
                                        <h3>How long does provider onboarding take?</h3>
                                        <p>End-to-end: 2-3 weeks per provider. Application + skill test + background check (1 week), training (1-2 weeks), trial jobs with mystery customer audit (1 week). Plan a separate operations team to scale onboarding.</p>
                                        <h3>How do I handle no-show cancellations?</h3>
                                        <p>24-hour cancellation policy with 50% refund, less-than-2-hour cancellation with no refund. If provider arrives and customer cancels, customer pays full provider compensation. Build the policy into the booking flow with explicit consent.</p>
                                        <h3>Should I focus on one service category or be a multi-category marketplace?</h3>
                                        <p>Start single category in one city for the first 6-12 months. Build supply-side moat. Expand to adjacent categories (salon to massage to nails) before geographic expansion. Urban Company spent 4 years on salon-only before scaling categories.</p>
